The paper focuses on physical human-robot interaction, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework uses reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves modeling uncertainty using Gaussian processes, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The task involves vision-based control, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of equal role sharing between human and robot partners, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
